HEADWORD: Gyromancy
<hw>Gyr"o*man`cy</hw> <pr>(j⟦icr⟧r"⟦osl⟧*m⟦acr⟧n`s⟦ycr⟧ ⟦or⟧
j⟦imac⟧"r⟦osl⟧-)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>gy^ros</grk> ring,
circle + <ets>-mancy</ets>: cf. F. <ets>gyromancie</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
kind of divination performed by drawing a ring or circle, and walking in
or around it.</def> <rj><au>Brande & C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

